1 collaboration with the valued members of the committee, continues to emphasize the
2 importance of "boots-on-the-ground" advocacy and the strengthening of personal
3 relationships between farmers and their elected officials; and
4 WHEREAS, fostering a deeper understanding of the labor and dedication required
5 to maintain Louisiana's diverse agricultural landscape, from timber and sugarcane to rice,
6 poultry, and crawfish, is essential for the development of sound public policy.
7 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
8 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate the week of March 23 though 27, 2026, as
9 Louisiana Agriculture Week at the state capitol and in the state of Louisiana and does hereby
10 commend the farmers, ranchers, and agribusiness leaders of this state for their participation
11 in this initiative and for their invaluable contributions to Louisiana's economy, food security,
12 and cultural heritage.
13 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the Legislature
14 of Louisiana does hereby encourage all citizens and lawmakers to participate in activities
15 that celebrate and support the hardworking men and women of Louisiana agriculture.
16 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a suitable copy of this Resolution be transmitted
17 to the commissioner of agriculture and the president of the Louisiana Farm Bureau
18 Federation.
